// Phase 6.2.A — hangar facility class shapes. Per Design/fleet.md and
// Design/social/facilities-and-ownership.md, hangars come in two tiers,
// both authored from the same template. The tier governs which slot
// classes are housed (surface = MS / fighter / MW; drydock = capital).
//
// Each row is keyed by a building-type id (in building-types.json5) and
// carries the *facility-class* shape — capacities, storage caps, daily
// economics that don't fit cleanly on BuildingType. Only one tier
// (`hangarSurface`) is actually placed at Phase 6.2.A; the drydock row
// is authored here so the schema locks in for 6.2.A.2 / 6.2.C2 without
// a follow-up data churn.
//
// Slot classes:
//   ms          — mobile-suit-sized bay (20m frames). Surface tier only.
//   smallCraft  — fighters / mobile workers / shuttles. Both tiers.
//   capital     — cruiser / battleship slip. Drydock tier only.
//
// Capacity-only verbs ship at 6.2.A; ShipStatSheet + persistent damage +
// repair throughput land at 6.2.B; supply/fuel storage drain + dealer
// orders at 6.2.F; transfer-to-other-hangar (paid + delayed) at 6.2.G or
// E2 (whichever defines the shipment-day infra first). Authoring those
// numerics here ahead of consumers would be speculative — keep this
// minimal, grow with each slice that needs more.

{
  hangars: {
    hangarSurface: {
      tier: 'surface',
      slotCapacity: { ms: 4, smallCraft: 4 },
    },
    hangarDrydock: {
      tier: 'drydock',
      slotCapacity: { capital: 4, smallCraft: 12 },
    },
  },
}
